summary: Parallel: Part 1 I Don’t Belong in A World Where You Don’t Exist
title: Parallel: Part 1 I Don’t Belong in A World Where You Don’t Exist
body:
A/N Hello this is my first try. I’m still new in things related to writing. So I apologize for the mistakes as english isn’t my first language. Critics and suggestions are welcomed. Enjoy

Trigger Warning: Angst, Suicide, Death

Masterlist Parallel: Prelude  Part 2

Present Time – After Infinity War

September 2018

Lacrimosa dies illa

Qua resurget ex favilla

Judicandus homo reus.

Huic ergo parce, Deus:

Pie Jesu Domine,

Dona eis requiem. Amen.

 “We are gathered here today, to honor those who have fallen, our heroes, our family, our friends and lovers. Humanity once again stand against the oppression and we survived, but we took a great cost.  Now it is the job of the living one to rebuild our nation, our planet, to take care and continue living for a greater future of humanity. As what Thomas Moore once said “Peace to each manly soul that sleepeth; Rest to each faithful eye that weepeth”……

The rest eulogy that being delivered no longer heard by (Y/N). She stared on those sleek black marble in front of her, where her friends name is written permanently in gold ink. To honor them, they said. Her eyes move along the names there; 

In memoriam: Steve Rogers, Tony Stark, Natasha Romanoff, Bruce Banner and Clint Barton. Written bellow it “Sit tibi terra levis, May the earth rest lightly on you”.

(Y/N) chuckled, well they probably will be mad knowing such lame eulogy written on their memoriam. But then again, she realized now that what happen is real. That they’re gone. Her family, friends, and lover. She’s alone, and it starts to sink in as her tears falls down her face, to the cold ground as it greeted by harsh wind of autumn. She feel numb, she doesn’t want to continue without them. How could she? After everything that happen with them, every single happy and loving memories, stressful talk before every mission, capsicle’s man-up-speech at the hovercraft or just being lazy with everyone at the common room. And now she can’t have that back.

(Y/N) decided it’s time to go back to the compound. She doesn’t want to hear those fake sympathy from people, or question from press of what went wrong or how it can lead to earth-mightiest hero’s demise. She just want to go back to her room and sleep for a long time.

Silence. Absolute silence. (Y/N) step in to the compound only to realize the horrible silence that now lingering the building. She move forward to their common room hoping for the slightest sound of their friends bickering over dinner menu or about who dump the coffee powder on the sink. Instead she got nothing. Only the sound of the clock ticking and the soft hump from the coffee machine greet her. It’s just too much. She used to hear Tony and Bruce bickering in their lab, occasionally little explosion and broken glass, she used to hear soft chat between Natasha and Clint about the next mission, the sound of Thor rummaging the fridge for poptarts, or the sound of Steve’s hand hitting the punch bag in the gym, or the soft squeak from bucky’s metal arm. Now, nothing can be heard.

“I just want you guys to come back to me. I can’t do this, please don’t do this to me”. (Y/N) sunk to the floor, her tears stream down her face, her funeral dress crumpled. She doesn’t care. She doesn’t want anything other than her family to come back. She first join the team to help them with Loki and after that New York Battle. She isn’t a mutant or enhanced human, she is just a normal human being. Her position as consultant and occasionally as the team’s doctor along with bruce makes her close with the so called avengers team and a certain person called Steve Rogers.

They become her family, her anchor to keep going on through the life. Her relationship with Steve develop during and after mission, and the fact that Steve proposed to her last month only adds another wound, and the only thing left for her to mourn is her engagement ring that she still wear. She was alone before them, her family involved in unfortunate road accident which killed her parents. And now she is all alone again.

Deciding she has too much, (Y/N) decided to stand. And walk to her and Steve room. She went to the bathroom, washing her face and looking on her reflection in the mirror. “I don’t belong in a world where you don’t exist. I don’t want too.” (Y/N) frantically search for any sleeping medication in the medicine cabinet, pushing the other bottle down the floor, and she finally found it. She walks to the kitchen to grab a glass of water along with the pills and return to their room. She closed the door and sit on the bed while she gently twist her engagement ring. This is it. This is the end. “I’m sorry Steve, I can’t go on without you”. She took a lot of pill and drink the water, feeling it slowly down her throat. She decided to lay down on her bed, her legs dangle from the side. She felt the sleeping pills start to work, lulling her to her final slumber.

“I’m Sorry. I’m so sorry”.

As the darkness begins to surround her, flashes of her memories with the team and with her Steve starts to envelope her. Her first meeting with the team, first mission, the time when steve asked her for a date, her first kiss with steve and the time when he propose to her. It calms her knowing at least now, she doesn’t have to feel anything. And everything went black.

She decided to lay down on her bed, her legs dangle from the side. She felt the sleeping pills start to work, lulling her to her final slumber.

“I’m Sorry. I’m so sorry”.

As the darkness begins to surround her, flashes of her memories with the team and with her Steve starts to envelope her. Her first meeting with the team, first mission, the time when steve asked her for a date, her first kiss with steve and the time when he propose to her. It calms her knowing at least now, she doesn’t have to feel anything. And everything went black.

A/N Hello this is my first try. I’m still new in things related to writing. So I apologize for the mistakes as english isn’t my first language. Critics and suggestions are welcomed. Enjoy

Trigger Warning: Angst, Suicide, Death

Masterlist Parallel: Prelude  Part 2

Present Time – After Infinity War

September 2018

Lacrimosa dies illa

Qua resurget ex favilla

Judicandus homo reus.

Huic ergo parce, Deus:

Pie Jesu Domine,

Dona eis requiem. Amen.

 “We are gathered here today, to honor those who have fallen, our heroes, our family, our friends and lovers. Humanity once again stand against the oppression and we survived, but we took a great cost.  Now it is the job of the living one to rebuild our nation, our planet, to take care and continue living for a greater future of humanity. As what Thomas Moore once said “Peace to each manly soul that sleepeth; Rest to each faithful eye that weepeth”……

The rest eulogy that being delivered no longer heard by (Y/N). She stared on those sleek black marble in front of her, where her friends name is written permanently in gold ink. To honor them, they said. Her eyes move along the names there; 

In memoriam: Steve Rogers, Tony Stark, Natasha Romanoff, Bruce Banner and Clint Barton. Written bellow it “Sit tibi terra levis, May the earth rest lightly on you”.

(Y/N) chuckled, well they probably will be mad knowing such lame eulogy written on their memoriam. But then again, she realized now that what happen is real. That they’re gone. Her family, friends, and lover. She’s alone, and it starts to sink in as her tears falls down her face, to the cold ground as it greeted by harsh wind of autumn. She feel numb, she doesn’t want to continue without them. How could she? After everything that happen with them, every single happy and loving memories, stressful talk before every mission, capsicle’s man-up-speech at the hovercraft or just being lazy with everyone at the common room. And now she can’t have that back.

(Y/N) decided it’s time to go back to the compound. She doesn’t want to hear those fake sympathy from people, or question from press of what went wrong or how it can lead to earth-mightiest hero’s demise. She just want to go back to her room and sleep for a long time.

Silence. Absolute silence. (Y/N) step in to the compound only to realize the horrible silence that now lingering the building. She move forward to their common room hoping for the slightest sound of their friends bickering over dinner menu or about who dump the coffee powder on the sink. Instead she got nothing. Only the sound of the clock ticking and the soft hump from the coffee machine greet her. It’s just too much. She used to hear Tony and Bruce bickering in their lab, occasionally little explosion and broken glass, she used to hear soft chat between Natasha and Clint about the next mission, the sound of Thor rummaging the fridge for poptarts, or the sound of Steve’s hand hitting the punch bag in the gym, or the soft squeak from bucky’s metal arm. Now, nothing can be heard.

“I just want you guys to come back to me. I can’t do this, please don’t do this to me”. (Y/N) sunk to the floor, her tears stream down her face, her funeral dress crumpled. She doesn’t care. She doesn’t want anything other than her family to come back. She first join the team to help them with Loki and after that New York Battle. She isn’t a mutant or enhanced human, she is just a normal human being. Her position as consultant and occasionally as the team’s doctor along with bruce makes her close with the so called avengers team and a certain person called Steve Rogers.

They become her family, her anchor to keep going on through the life. Her relationship with Steve develop during and after mission, and the fact that Steve proposed to her last month only adds another wound, and the only thing left for her to mourn is her engagement ring that she still wear. She was alone before them, her family involved in unfortunate road accident which killed her parents. And now she is all alone again.

Deciding she has too much, (Y/N) decided to stand. And walk to her and Steve room. She went to the bathroom, washing her face and looking on her reflection in the mirror. “I don’t belong in a world where you don’t exist. I don’t want too.” (Y/N) frantically search for any sleeping medication in the medicine cabinet, pushing the other bottle down the floor, and she finally found it. She walks to the kitchen to grab a glass of water along with the pills and return to their room. She closed the door and sit on the bed while she gently twist her engagement ring. This is it. This is the end. “I’m sorry Steve, I can’t go on without you”. She took a lot of pill and drink the water, feeling it slowly down her throat. She decided to lay down on her bed, her legs dangle from the side. She felt the sleeping pills start to work, lulling her to her final slumber.

“I’m Sorry. I’m so sorry”.

As the darkness begins to surround her, flashes of her memories with the team and with her Steve starts to envelope her. Her first meeting with the team, first mission, the time when steve asked her for a date, her first kiss with steve and the time when he propose to her.
